## Release-discipline rule — quick reference

**Done** (new rule-definition of "done", applied for every BUILD-repo session going forward):

1. PR merged to main ✅
2. `/release` run in the same session ✅
3. Package index (PyPI/crates.io) shows new version via `info.version` metadata
4. Clean-venv `pip install <pkg>==<new> && python -c "from <pkg> import <new-surface>"` succeeds ← **the done-gate**

Reporting done at step 1 or 2 is BLOCKED. Deferring step 3-4 to "next session" is BLOCKED. Releasing only the modified package (ignoring stale siblings) is BLOCKED. All enumerated in `.claude/rules/build-repo-release-discipline.md`.
